    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Built-in types like `int` and `long` have unspecified bit widths and representations. We should prefer sized integer types like `uint32_t` and `int16_t`.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I should clarify here, that in `printf()` and `LOGGER_*`, sized ints should explicitly not be used, because format specifiers like `%d` expect `int` specifically. In all code *except* format-string function calls, we should use sized integer types. This is the \"most\" part of the bug sentence.",
            "created_at": "2018-07-16T16:49:43Z",
